</tbody></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufynalwiz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fynalwiz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 750<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/3/02 9:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Real Caster Balance</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  I have yet to see any convicing argument for this widely accepted &quot;start weak and end balanced&quot; theory that didn't depend on twinking. Everyone just seems to accept it as true. What if everyone is wrong and it's just a massively overpowering jump in power when you hit 60? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I can't really speak on below 50, now, because I have no idea what its like with the recent changes. Here is what I know, there are three things that I feel have boosted my power immensly in my 50s.<br>
<br>
1.) Draughts: 688 max damage or so for 215 mana with a 3 sec cast time. This does more damage then Conflag--a lvl 44 wizzie favoritye--but costs less mana and is some 2.5 seconds faster. There is no spell, at any point before 51, that rivals the mana efficieny of Draughts. Furthermore, to find a spell that is as fast as a DoF, you have to go all the way back to lvl 16 for Ice Shock. That is a killer combo, that really represents a huge boost in wizard power.<br>
<br>
2.) KEI: This spell makes me feel like I am approaching where I need to be in a fast pulling group. But I need that along with...<br>
<br>
3.) A couple focus items: Naki's ring I believe, plus Gallenites bracer, lowers the DoF cast time to 2.5 secs and up your average damage per cast to around 700. Relatively speaking, that is sick damage, done very cheap, and very efficiently. The final touch however is....<br>
<br>
4.) Draught of Ice: At 59, casting DoI, with Gallenite's Bracer and the ring, I can easily hit for 800 or so, with a 2.5 sec cast time, and a mana cost of about 215. Truly amazing, compared to what i was doing only 10 levels ago.<br>
<br>
I feel--not know because I dont have the logs--that when I have all of these things clicking, I am about where I should be. I can only dream about what it would mean to have these MC3, SCM, Improved Flappy and crits (with KEI on we are talking about a mana regen at about 23per tick, if just manaskin is on. That is a mana regen number, that I can't even fathom). I would have to think, that at that point, I would be about balanced. <br>
<br>
How does this spike in power compare to other classes? I can't really say, as I have not done the research. But I know that at 59, I feel like I am about thrice the wizard I was at 49. <br>
<br>
