Though I cannot offer proof, I can offer what I would hope is a convincing argument supporting the &quot;start weak&quot; end of the theory. It does not depend on twinking, but it does depend on mudflation. About a year ago I started a ranger on a newish server so I could play casually with some RL friends. By hunting (almost exclusively) bats and skeletons and selling stacks of wings for 1pp, and stacks of chips for 2-3pp. By level 5 I was able to accumulate about 25pp, which I could use to purchase a frozen longsword (MAGIC, 7/27), which is roughly twice as good as any weapon I could acquire by myself at that level, as well as a full set of patchwork armor from a tailor who was working up her skill. This translated directly into doing double the damage I did before, and when soloing that translates into taking half damage from foes. From there I had started harvesting and selling orc belts for sale, but I abandoned that character at level 7.<br>
<br>
The only wizard item which gives anything close to that level of power increase is the Solist Wand, which is quite rare and sells for about 5k (which makes it a twink item), and it's power band of use is 16-35 or so.<br>
<br>
I could try the same exercise today and I would undoubtedly find the situation at low levels even more heavily skewed toward melee (Centi weapons are evil).<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I get quoted spell numbers and such then have people telling me that their wizards are soloing mobs on 2 bubs of mana at level 25. /boggle when I was 25 as a mage I remember spending tons more than 2 bubs of mana soloing stuff in loio.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I can't really comment on this. When I was 25 I could not solo effectively at all. I pretty much required a group. Root/Nuke (the only viable strategy at that level) was painful because root took a fairly large portion of my spell points at that level and usually needed to be cast multiple times. If I had a solist wand at that level I could solo very well, but that's quite unusual. It may also be that these numbers are quoted against light blue cons, and I think you'll find this sort of thing to be more common now than it was when you were leveling up.<br>
